strategy: Combine early fact filtering with zip condition decorrelation: (1) Create CTEs for all filtered dimensions with selective predicates pushed down; (2) Pre-filter store_sales by ss_wholesale_cost and jo
what_worked: Applied date_cte_isolate, multi_dimension_prefetch: Created selective CTEs for each filtered dimension, pre-joined store_sales with date and item first to reduce fact rows early, then applied zip inequality filter after joining customer address and store. This reduces the fact table early and transforms the query into an optimal join order.
why_it_worked: Pre-filtering date dimension into CTE reduces hash join probe table from 73K to ~365 rows; Pre-filtering multiple dimension tables in parallel reduces join fan-out
